<br>
For the sake of discussion, I assume that once engaged in battle, the pet would acquire aggravation normally, like any combatant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Consequences I see off the top of my head:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bad pathing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would have fewer negative consequences for pets and pet owners.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would likely be eliminated, except possibly in some rare circumstances that could be fixed.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pet Utility</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would be increased in raids and dungeons.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pet Risk</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would be dramatically reduced.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Air Pet's Invisibility</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would become worthless.<br>
<br>
What other consequences, negative and positive, do you see?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Abuser of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_useezcodes.html">EZCodes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
