<br>
I agree.  But that's just the problem.  In many situations the risk vs. reward of having pets up is so bad that it's simply not worth using them.  That severly hinders the Mages usefulness to the encounter, as it's been shown that pets typically account for about half of a Mages overall average damage.<br>
<br>
So if risk vs. reward is out of balance, then pet usefulness needs to be increased through greater damage output.  Which brings us back to the AFK experience problem.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
