</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 695<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/02 5:03:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Consequences of Indifferent Pets</span><hr size=1> This is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;brain storming&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> session, whose purpose is to come up with as many ideas as possible in an effort to cover as many bases as possible.  Criticizing or evaluating the ideas, while instinctive, is not really appropriate at this stage.<br>
<br>
If this is really what we want, we must be prepared to meet as many objections from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as possible.<br>
<br>
As logs elsewhere in this forum seem to suggest, except perhaps in raids, pet damage output is likely to be close to adequate.  Therefore, dramatic improvements in damage are unlikely.  Therefore, we must we look to another avenues to improve <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> pet utility</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> seems a promising approach.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> if they were non social but kos, the mage could just single pull them and kill them that way. the mage can do this already.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->My conclusion as well.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> saying air pets invisibility becomming &quot;worthless&quot; is a consequence of making pets indifferent to everything, is like saying a strip of diseased cloth being used as a make-shift bandage becomming &quot;worthless&quot; is a consequence of having your wound professionally treated in a sterile hostpital.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well we are trying to brainstorm consequences, and that is certainly one of them.  Currently, if you want to do the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet sit down, Summon Companion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> trick to bring your pet along through a difficult travel, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Air</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet works best exactly because of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Invisibility</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, any pet can be towed around in this many, and further, he can be parked anyway.  It makes all pets essentially invisible to all mobs, undead or not.  This is not a trivial matter.  True, it would also greatly reduce the need for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet sit down, Summon Companion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but there are places where it still would be required.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, it would allow us to park our pets <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>anywhere</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, even right in the middle of a spawn.  Surely there must be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>some</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> consequence of that.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> there is litterally - no down side - to making pets indifferent con to all mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Perhaps in your mind, but to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this will surely be seen as opening up a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pandora's Box</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Here's a scenario I can easily imagine.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tries out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> indifferent pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Test Server</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> community would <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>expect</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> this change to become live, and would feel betrayed if it did not.  Suppose no problems are found on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Test</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which after all has a small population, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> indifferent pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> goes live.<br>
<br>
After a month or two, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sacred Band of Dudes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, an uber-guild, discovers an exploit which <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;invalidates content.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Time to get out the nerf bat.  If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> withdraws <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> indifferent pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> community will be outraged.  If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> attempts some other quick but brutal <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;fix&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Law of Unintended Consequences</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> comes into play, and again, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are likely to feel pain.  Imagine our suffering if after two monthes of being allowed on raids because the risk of pets has become acceptable, and then having it withdrawn.  It would be like being cast from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Paradise</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  So <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would likely only have bad choices.<br>
<br>
We <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>are</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> talking about a dramatic change to game play.  It would be akin to changing one of the fundamental constants in physics, like the speed of light, or the Planck length.  It <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>will</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> have unanticipated consequences.  We best be prepared.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> would making pets indiff to all have any affect on the elemental or skelly illusions? Im not sure if both are linked in some way. If so there is no way they would do this.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->While I do not know how the specific code works, I do know that they can distinguish between pets and PCs, and can attach effects to buffs.  So if they wish to retain <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> KOS</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Forms</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, it seems to me that it would not be difficult to encode.<br>
<br>
Except perhaps for exploits we do not yet see, it seems clear that the biggest impact would be a dramatic shift in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Risk versus Reward</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for pets, one that is difficult to evaluate.  All of a sudden, places where pets would be useless would be open to us.  Pet control would be much easier.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Risk versus Reward</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the key.  We must argue on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s terms, since <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;We're in their world now.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The argument should go something like this.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as it has been long known, pay a number of significant penalties for having <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br>
We are the only caster class that lacks <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Root, Fear,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Snare</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
We are exceedingly vulnerable without our pets.<br>
Our contribution to groups and raids is significantly less without our pets.<br>
We pay an experience penalty for having pets.<br>
Pets disappear when we zone or go linkdead.  No other class loses such a great portion of their power when they zone.<br>
No other class, except perhaps <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wizards</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, is so vulnerable upon logging in.<br>
We are vulnerable to flaws in the design and implementation of the game through no fault of our own.  We did not invent pathing, but we live and die by it.<br>
Our pets, while melee based, do not scale post-50, and become weaker relative to our enemies as we rise in level.<br>
<br>
Considering the enormous costs associated with having <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the rewards should be corresponding great.<br>
And these include &lt;insert exhaustive list of pet advantages here&gt;.<br>
<br>
However, in entirely too many situations, especially during the course of ordinary endgame activities, the risk of maintaining our valued pets is so great, that we must do without, or risk the death of all our companions.<br>
<br>
So we find ourselves often crippled, and in limited demand.<br>
<br>
And so, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Karana, Greatest of All Gods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, we submit this humble petition: that <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Elementals</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be made indifferent to mobs, so that we may travel to those places which we have been forbidden or crippled, and aid our boon companions.<br>
<br>
&lt;list of positive benefits to Magicians and obvious consequences&gt;<br>
<br>
We realize, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Oh Great Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that this change will likely shake the world like Thunder!  But since when does the God of Storms fear Thunder?<br>
<br>
&lt;evaluation of possible negative consequences, and proposed solutions if necessary&gt;<br>
<br>
In any case, if this is indeed what we want, we need to figure out the consequences ahead of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and be prepared to answer them in advance.  If pet power is close to adequate except on raids, that can be fixed later after the consequences of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> indifferent pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> becomes clear, along with the role of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in this new world.<br>
<br>
And yes, I think we should petition <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Better results than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gordon</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I suspect.<br>
<br>
