One negative impact I could see is that if the pet is indifferent you cannot &quot;scrape off&quot; an add onto a pet already in combat with a different species of mob or a nonsocial species of the same mob.<br>
<br>
This is tricky enough to do as it is now. Let's say the pet is in melee with a frost giant in GD. Along comes a direwolf that aggro's the mage simply by proximity. <br>
 Mage runs through the pet (getting some distance due to jboots or SoW) and hopes the direwolf will redirect aggro to pet.<br>
<br>
Ignoring the obvious and frequently futile use of /pet back off there is no way if the pet was indifferent that the direwolf would aggro the pet and leave the mage.<br>
<br>
I think this is a fairly minor consequence of making pet's indifferent so don't spend too much time shooting holes in it. I'm just brainstorming as suggested.<br>
<br>
On an related note maybe JayTee should ask his guild about what use they may find for an indifferent pet. Not to imply that FoH would exploit anything on purpose but certainly they seem to be a crafty bunch of stratigists. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-Singha Overcast <BR>
